wikibaselexeme-lemma-edit-placeholder: Lemma is usually the shortest form of the word
wikibaselexeme-lemma-redundant-language: It is not possible to enter multiple lemmas with the same spelling variant.
wikibaselexeme-form-representation-redun: It is not possible to enter multiple representations with the same spelling variant.
wikibaselexeme-sense-gloss-invalid-langu: Gloss language codes must be valid
wikibaselexeme-sense-gloss-redundant-lan: It is not possible to enter multiple glosses with the same language.
wikibase-listdatatypes-wikibase-lexeme-b: Link to lexemes on the project. When a value is entered, the project's "Lexeme" namespace will be searched for matching lexemes.
wikibase-listdatatypes-wikibase-form-bod: Link to forms on the project. When a value is entered, the project's "Lexeme" namespace will be searched for matching forms.
wikibase-listdatatypes-wikibase-sense-bo: Link to senses on the project. When a value is entered, the project's "Lexeme" namespace will be searched for matching senses.
apihelp-wbladdform-param-lexemeId: ID of the lexeme, e.g. L10
apihelp-wbladdform-param-data: JSON encoded data for form i.e. representations and grammatical features
apihelp-wbladdform-param-bot: Mark this edit as bot. This URL flag will only be respected if the user belongs to the group "{{int:group-bot}}".
apihelp-wbladdform-example-1: Add form to the lexeme with ID <samp>$1</samp> having representations <samp>$2</samp> with languages <samp>$3</samp> respectively and grammatical features <samp>$4</samp>
apihelp-wblremoveform-param-id: ID of the form, e.g. L10-F20
apihelp-wblremoveform-param-bot: Mark this edit as bot. This URL flag will only be respected if the user belongs to the group "{{int:group-bot}}".
apihelp-wblremoveform-example-1: Remove Form from the lexeme with ID <samp>$1</samp>
apihelp-wbleditformelements-summary: Edits representations and grammatical features of a form
apihelp-wbleditformelements-param-formId: ID of the form, e.g. L10-F2
apihelp-wbleditformelements-param-data: JSON-encoded representation and grammatical feature data
apihelp-wbleditformelements-param-bot: Mark this edit as bot. This URL flag will only be respected if the user belongs to the group "{{int:group-bot}}".
apihelp-wbleditformelements-example-1: Edits form with the ID <samp>$1</samp> to have representations <samp>$2</samp> in languages <samp>$3</samp> respectively, and grammatical features <samp>$4</samp>.
apihelp-wbladdsense-summary: Adds a sense to a lexeme
apihelp-wbladdsense-param-lexemeId: ID of the lexeme, e.g. L10
apihelp-wbladdsense-param-data: JSON-encoded data for the sense, i.e. its glosses
apihelp-wbladdsense-param-bot: Mark this edit as bot. This URL flag will only be respected if the user belongs to the group "{{int:group-bot}}".
apihelp-wbladdsense-example-1: Add a form to the lexeme with ID <samp>$1</samp> having glosses <samp>$2</samp> with languages <samp>$3</samp> respectively
apihelp-wblremovesense-param-id: ID of the sense, e.g. L10-S20
apihelp-wblremovesense-param-bot: Mark this edit as bot. This URL flag will only be respected if the user belongs to the group "{{int:group-bot}}".
apihelp-wblremovesense-example-1: Remove sense from the lexeme with ID <samp>$1</samp>
apihelp-wbleditsenseelements-param-sense: ID of the sense, e.g. L10-S2
apihelp-wbleditsenseelements-param-bot: Mark this edit as bot. This URL flag will only be respected if the user belongs to the group "{{int:group-bot}}".
apihelp-wbleditsenseelements-example-1: Edits sense with the ID <samp>$1</samp> to have glosses <samp>$2</samp> in languages <samp>$3</samp> respectively.
apihelp-query+wbcontentlanguages-paramva: The terms of a lexicographical entity (lemmas of a lexeme, representations of a form, or glosses of a sense).
apihelp-wblmergelexemes-param-summary:
Summary for the edit.
Will be prepended by an automatically generated comment. The length limit of the autocomment together with the summary is 260 characters. Be aware that everything above that limit will be cut off.
apihelp-wblmergelexemes-param-bot: Mark this edit as bot. This URL flag will only be respected if the user belongs to the group "bot".
wikibaselexeme-error-cannot-remove-last-: An error has occurred: The last lemma cannot be removed.
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-inval: Parameter "$1" expected to be a valid JSON object, given "$2"
wikibaselexeme-api-error-lexeme-not-foun: Field "$1" contains an ID of a lexeme "$2" that could not be found.
wikibaselexeme-api-error-form-not-found: Field "$1" contains an ID of a form "$2" that could not be found.
wikibaselexeme-api-error-sense-not-found: Field "$1" contains an ID of a sense "$2" that could not be found.
wikibaselexeme-api-error-json-field-requ: Field "$3" at "$2" in parameter "$1" is required
wikibaselexeme-api-error-json-field-not-: Field "$2" in parameter "$1" expected to be an item ID. Given: "$3"
wikibaselexeme-api-error-json-field-has-: Field "$2" in parameter "$1" expected to be of type "$3". Given: "$4"
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-not-l: Parameter "$1" expected to be a lexeme ID. Given: "$2"
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-not-f: Field "$2" in parameter "$1" expected to be a form ID. Given: "$3"
wikibaselexeme-api-error-parameter-not-s: Field "$2" in parameter "$1" expected to be a sense ID. Given: "$3"
wikibaselexeme-api-error-language-incons: Language in field "$1" at "$2" was expected to be "$3". Given: "$4"
wikibaselexeme-api-error-form-must-have-: Form must have at least one representation
wikibaselexeme-api-error-sense-must-have: Sense must have at least one gloss
wikibaselexeme-api-error-invalid-item-id: Invalid item ID "$3" in field "$1" at "$2".
wikibase-lexeme-summary-update-form-repr: Changed representations and/or grammatical features of form $3
wikibase-lexeme-summary-update-form-gram: Changed representations and/or grammatical features of form $3
wikibase-lexeme-summary-update-form-elem: Changed representations and/or grammatical features of form $3
wikibase-validator-form-not-found: Lexeme does not have form with given ID
wikibaselexeme-grammatical-features-inpu: For example: normative, comparative, past tense...
wikibase-lexeme-lemma-language-not-recog: The supplied language code was not recognized.
wikibase-lexeme-mergelexemes-intro: If you merge two lexemes, all lemmas, statements, forms and senses will be moved from one lexeme to the other.
wikibase-lexeme-mergelexemes-error-inval: '$1' is not a valid lexeme ID
wikibase-lexeme-mergelexemes-error-confl: Failed to merge lexemes, please resolve any conflicts first. Error: Lexemes have different lemmas for the same spelling variant.
wikibase-lexeme-mergelexemes-error-cross: Failed to merge lexemes, please resolve any conflicts first. Error: Lexemes link to each other in a statement.
wikibase-lexeme-mergelexemes-error-same-: Failed to merge lexemes, please resolve any conflicts first. Error: Lexemes have different languages.
Failed to merge lexemes, please resolve any conflicts first. Error: Lexemes have different lexical categories.
wikibase-lexeme-mergelexemes-error-faile: Failed to merge lexemes, please resolve any conflicts first.
wikibase-lexeme-mergelexemes-error-same-: Cannot merge a lexeme with itself.
